We DO stand in the lines, but receive a return time so much of our wait time has been somewhere else (sitting down, using the restrooms, going to First Aid, etc). I hope you enjoy the video!

node.text:
Sharon Quirk-Silva was interviewed outside of Disneyland today. She shared her thoughts about the Governors decision not to allow theme parks such as Disneyland to reopen until the county has reached the yellow tier. I wasn’t sure if my iPhone was picking up what she was saying so I tried to ensure I reiterated most of what she was saying. Disneyland is pushing hard to reopen. It’ll be interesting to see what happens as this is the first time in Disneyland history that the park has been shut down for such an extensive period of time.
.

node.text:
This is totally outside of the typical content I create and post, but I felt so strongly that this specific scene in the Netflix documentary Schitts Creek Best Wishes, Warmest Regards needed to be shared. Forgive me, you can hear me sniffling and crying as I filmed this. Schitts Creek is one of my favorite shows and has served as a super catalyst for acceptance, love, and positive personification of the LGBTQ+ community. I share some of my own thoughts and feelings (not very eloquently bc I had a hard time NOT crying) after the scene. I absolutely love that I am seeing more and more support LGBTQ+ community, but I also experience a devastating amount of hate on a daily basis. My goal behind our social media has been and will continue to be to offer ppl a small glimpse into our lives as a family in the hopes that we might open a few minds and hearts along the way. Love is love ❤️ And I hope and pray we see more and more queer representation in movies, television shows, books, etc. 🏳️‍🌈✊🏽 @schittscreek @instadanjlevy @annefrances 
.
.

I can't tell you how much I wish ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs was available when I brought Ariel home. It was developed specifically for rescue dogs! ACANA created a food that not only supports your new pups immune system, but also helps with digestion. ACANA Rescue Care for Adopted Dogs can help make welcoming your new family member home a positive experience for you and your sweet pup! Now you won't have to stand in the dog food aisle the same way I did wondering if you're making the right choice or not. ACANA took the stress out of choosing a dog food for your rescue dog!

node.text:
Our pathetic attempt at a family photo in Downtown Disney 😂 Evan was irritated that Ella had her arm around him, Jace clearly didn’t understand the assignment, Mya is trying to tickle Eli to get him to turn in the right direction, I’m yelling “SMIIIIIIIIILE!” at the top of my lungs, and right when we snapped this shot a family walked into the background that hadn’t been there 🤣🤣 I learned a long time ago that “perfect” doesn’t exist especially when it comes to family.

As I sit here in our living room convinced one of these kids pooped bc I know I smell something rank, yelling at Evan and Ella to stop fighting, telling Eli to stop throwing toys across the room, and just generally feeling like I need a nap even though I’ve only been up for a few hours, I can’t help but laugh 😆 I may be tired, but the reality of my life always makes me laugh! But it wasn’t always that way.

When people meet us in person one of the most common things they tell me is we are the same as we are on camera. I have to laugh because there’s no hiding this sh*t show 🤣🤣 I’ve tried for years to hide who we are because I was made to feel ashamed and embarrassed by other moms. Not being the perfect mom in a family with extraordinary issues was held against me by other women who had NO idea what it’s been like to deal with the kind of pressure and stress I’ve dealt with for years as a parent. Going out in public was always incredibly anxiety provoking for me 😬 and I struggled with it for years.

Starting our YouTube channel and being open and honest about what our family is like has honestly been so freeing! It’s inevitable that at least one of us will be crying or having some sort of breakdown (might be me 😂), I WILL be yelling at at least one of my kids pretty much throughout the day, and my kids will be playing it fast and loose with the personal boundaries of complete strangers bc that’s what they do 🤦🏻‍♀️ This is us! Not stressing about how others perceive us has been liberating. We are a complete sh*t show & I wouldn’t have it any other way 🌈

Happy #nationaldogday 🐕 to all those celebrating the day with their canine companions and to those whose 4 legged family members have crossed over the rainbow bridge 🌈

4 out of 6 cooperating for this photo ain’t bad! 😂😂 Our furry family members have always been an integral part of our lives. The love, patience, and loyalty shown to us by our dogs is priceless. I know the pain of having to say my final goodbyes to a beloved fur-mate. It’s incredibly painful and knowing that our pets are gifted to us for only so long makes us value each day spent with them even more! So let’s meet the McLeod Pups:

Ariel is approx a 6 or 7 years old rescue Lab. I met her in Texas when a friend of mine was fostering her. She was found in the valley completely starved and pregnant with 5 pups. I remember returning home and telling Gam Gams I had just met the dog with the saddest eyes I’d ever seen. Ariel has struggled with anxiety and had to learn how to “dog.” It was clear she had been abused so building trust with her took awhile. Slowly, she began blossoming into this happy, healthy girl who loves zoomies and snuggle bumping 🥰

Tinkerbell is an adopted rescue chihuahua and is between 5 and 8 years old. I adopted her last October and she’s turned out to be quite the diva 😂 Tinky loves being held, stealing the kids Wishables and hiding them in her kennel, and snacking on all kinds of yummy treats! She loves having a companion (Ariel) and acts as her backup whenever Ariel starts barking. She’s clearly not a model as you can tell from this blurry image of her 😂 I did my best! 🤣🤣

“A dog is the only thing on earth that loves you more than He loves Himself.” 🐶

If you’re local pls consider donating to @apurposefulrescue or @therealbark 🐕 Both organizations do so much for these sweet angels!
